HEADWORD: Fibrolite
<hw>Fi"bro*lite</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fibra</ets> a fiber + <ets>-lite</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>fibrolithe</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A silicate of
alumina, of fibrous or columnar structure. It is like andalusite in
composition; -- called also <altname>sillimanite</altname>, and
<altname>bucholzite</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fibroma</ent>⟦br⟧
